Brothers","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"All three Whiskey Brothers return to the stage for their 8th Annual Drunken Christmas Ball, and they're bring friends this time!  Regular podcast contributors Dale Cheesman and Kiki Maroon will make appearances, along with an entire host of Houston comedy alumni returning home for the holidays.  Who?  We can't tell you yet, but trust us when we say this is THE biggest comedy show to hit Houston in several years.  Featuring music by the Jeremy James Band.

Robert L. Mungle has an IMDB page with over 100 credits, including Akame ga Kill!, Ghost Stories, Lady Death, and Excel Saga.  As the founding member of the Whiskey Brothers, he's been sipping cocktails and regaling fans with tales of his exploits for over twenty years.

Slade Ham has performed in 41 countries on six continents.  He's been seen on A&E, WGN, at Just for Laughs, and most recently, was the subject of the documentary "I Am Battle Comic" directed by Jordan Brady ("Waking Up in Reno" and "I Am Comic") centered on his most recent tour through Afghanistan. Slade’s is a familiar voice to comedy-radio listeners, who laugh along to his three albums on Raw Dog and Blue Collar Comedy stations, though they might know him best from his regular appearances on The Bob & Tom Show.   In addition to touring domestically, Slade also works closely with Armed Forces Entertainment and produces his own international tours for the men and women in uniform across the globe. He is the founder of Operation: Punchline, an organization designed to help combat the veteran suicide rate (a staggering 22 a day) that provides free downloads of comedy albums for current and former military members and their spouses.  

Sam Demaris was recently picked as on e of Funny or Die's "Top Ten Comedians to Follow on Twitter."
